      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * David E. Welsh</b>\n</p><p><b>David E. Welsh</b>,<br />\nan American master-level chess player in the 80s who was involved in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Chess_Federation\">USCF</a> computer-rating activities testing <a href=\"/Dedicated_Chess_Computers\" title=\"Dedicated Chess Computers\">dedicated chess computers</a> and giving them a \"sanctioned USCF rating\" that could be used on packaging and advertising. \nHe was pretty knowledgeable about the subject of computer chess, attended many <a href=\"/ACM_North_American_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"ACM North American Computer Chess Championship\">ACM chess events</a> to discuss computer chess ideas with many participants <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>, \nand wrote several books and reports on that topic.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_E._Welsh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David E. Welsh</a> (<b>1980</b>). <i>Rating Boris 2.5</i>. <a href=\"/Personal_Computing#4_10\" title=\"Personal Computing\">Personal Computing, Vol. 4, No. 10</a>, pp. 78&#160;» <a href=\"/Boris#2.5\" title=\"Boris\">Boris 2.5</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David E. Welsh</a> (<b>1980</b>). <i>Rating Boris 2.5 - Part II</i>. <a href=\"/Personal_Computing#4_11\" title=\"Personal Computing\">Personal Computing, Vol. 4, No. 11</a>, pp. 87 </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David E. Welsh</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Computer Chess</i>.  William C Brown Publications, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Computer-chess-David-E-Welsh/dp/0697099008\">amazon</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David E. Welsh</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Super Constellation: It's Time for Skeptics to Take a Second Look at Chess Computers</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess_Life\">Chess Life</a>, November 1984, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/Chess_Life_1984_-_Novag_Super_Constellation.pdf\">pdf</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Super_Constellation\" title=\"Super Constellation\">Super Constellation</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David E. Welsh</a>, <a href=\"/Boris_Baczynskyj\" title=\"Boris Baczynskyj\">Boris Baczynskyj</a> (<b>1985</b>). <i>Computer Chess II</i>. William C Brown Publications, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Computer-Chess-II-David-Welsh/dp/0697099113\">amazon</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David E. Welsh</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>ACM's Sixteenth North American Computer Chess Championship</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#8_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 8, No. 4</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/ACM_1985\" title=\"ACM 1985\">ACM 1985</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_E._Welsh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n83130344.html\">Welsh, David E. - LC Linked Data Service</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Library_of_Congress\">Library of Congress</a>)</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://reanimationlibrary.tumblr.com/post/2814683917/from-computer-chess-welsh-david-e-dubuque-ia\">From Computer Chess. Welsh, David E. Dubuque, IA</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_E._Welsh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=411349&amp;t=39455\">Re: An interesting book with some insights on Bob's Cray Blitz</a> by <a href=\"/Robert_Hyatt\" title=\"Robert Hyatt\">Robert Hyatt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 25, 2011</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/g/rec.games.chess.computer/c/kecoM_YlyAM/m/NiCnP8wRgnQJ\">Computer chess books</a> by <a href=\"/Bruce_Moreland\" title=\"Bruce Moreland\">Bruce Moreland</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, February 05, 1997</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.johnljerz.com/superduper/tlxdownloadsiteMAIN/id125.html\">Computer Chess by David E. Welsh</a> by <a href=\"/John_L._Jerz\" title=\"John L. Jerz\">John L. Jerz</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=39455\">An interesting book with some insights on Bob's Cray Blitz</a> by <a href=\"/Julien_Marcel\" title=\"Julien Marcel\">Julien Marcel</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 23, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Cray_Blitz\" title=\"Cray Blitz\">Cray Blitz</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=61543\">Transposition tables in Cray Blitz</a> by <a href=\"/Erin_Dame\" title=\"Erin Dame\">Erin Dame</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>,  September 26, 2016&#160;» <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table</a>, <a href=\"/Cray_Blitz\" title=\"Cray Blitz\">Cray Blitz</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a> (<b>1985</b>). <i>D.E. Welsh and B. Baczynskyj: Computer Chess II</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#8_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 8, No. 3</a> (review)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301004325\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.010 s